<td class="answercell">
    <div class="post-text"><pre><code>bundle install --path=&lt;path&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>From the <a href="http://gembundler.com/man/bundle-install.1.html" rel="nofollow">docs</a>.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>The location to install the gems in the bundle to. This defaults to
  the gem home, which is the location that gem install installs gems to.
  This means that, by default, gems installed without a --path setting
  will show up in gem list. This setting is a remembered option.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
